\'93You can use a terminal command to speed up the mouse movements beyond what the slider will give you in system settings! I had the same annoyance with my magic mouse. Open the terminal app and type:\
\
===================================\
defaults write -g com.apple.mouse.scaling 5.0\
===================================\
\
the number (5.0) here tells the system the relative speed. the most you can get with the slider is 3.0 i believe. You just need to restart the computer for it to take effect. Hope that helps!\
